  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If you hold a PRS (Passenger Reservation System) counter ticket and your seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train, you will not be able to board the train using that ticket. A waitlisted ticket does not guarantee a seat, and if it remains waitlisted at the time of departure, it is considered invalid for travel.\n\nIn terms of a refund, the rules may vary depending on the specific policies of the railway service you are using. Generally, if the waitlisted status does not convert to confirmed before the departure, you may not be eligible for a full refund. However, if you cancel a waitlisted ticket before the train departs, you may receive a certain percentage of the fare back depending on the cancellation policy.\n\nTo get accurate information about the refund amount and the process, it's best to check with the railway's guidelines or their customer service.",
